## Non-Functional Requirements Documentation

This section documents the **Non-Functional Requirements (NFRs)** of the **Hackathon Team Management System**. These requirements define the quality attributes and constraints of the system.

---

### NFR-01: Performance
**Description:**  
The system shall respond to user actions within an acceptable time limit.

**Specification:**  
- Page load time should not exceed 3 seconds under normal usage  
- System should support multiple users accessing concurrently  

---

### NFR-02: Security
**Description:**  
The system shall ensure secure access and protect user data.

**Specification:**  
- User authentication is mandatory for accessing system features  
- User credentials must not be visible or stored in plain text  
- Unauthorized users should not access restricted functionalities  

---

### NFR-03: Usability
**Description:**  
The system shall be easy to use and understand for all users.

**Specification:**  
- User interface should be simple and intuitive  
- Basic operations should be performed without prior training  
- Clear messages should be displayed for errors and confirmations  

---

### NFR-04: Reliability
**Description:**  
The system shall operate reliably during normal usage.

**Specification:**  
- System should handle invalid inputs without crashing  
- Data should be stored correctly and consistently  
- System should be available during the hackathon event duration  

---

